Title: Giorgio Armani Idole D' EDP  -  50 ml(For Women)
Description: Marrying the delectable mysteries of the Orient with a classic Italian touch, this luxury scent brings together all the elements fit for the ideal woman. Giorgio Armani Idole D’ is a magnificent tribute to the breathtaking woman who personifies charm and grace. Created by Bruno Jovanovic, this Eau de Parfum is made for the celebrated house of Armani. Citrus notes of bitter orange, extracts of juicy pear, spicy hints of ginger and aromatic davana make up a refreshing top note. This flows into a fragrant heart note composed of the sweet scent of rose loukoum, exotic hints of jasmine and the seductive aroma of saffron. The base note finishes off with resinous extracts of styrax, strong-scented vetiver and earthy notes of patchouli. You can wear this delightful floral woody fragrance redolent with warm and spicy accords for an exciting evening out. The enigmatic fragrance is ensconced in a beautifully sculpted crystal glass structure that radiates an opulent air. The rounded frame is decorated with circular waves with an elegant stopper. The bottle is shimmers with a golden hue which adds to its timeless and grandiose appeal. A spritz of this enchanting perfume and bask in the glorious and sensual aura of femininity.

Title: Elie Saab L'Eau Couture Eau de Toilette  -  90 ml(For Men, Women)
Description: L`Eau Couture is the olfactory continuation of the designer s Ready-to-Wear 2014 Spring-Summer collection, in which ethereal fabrics as light as petals chisel a magical fusion between woman and nature. It captures the ecstasy of nature blossoming in an urban springtime setting.For L`Eau Couture, Francis Kurkdjian dreamed up a brand new tribute to freshness, which he leads into sensuality characterised by absolute sophistication. L`Eau Couture reinterprets accords in a way never seen before."The idea to create a Couture Eau is quite uncommon in this register. It s a sophisticated, sensual freshness, far removed from the conventions found in fragrances usually created in this repertoire" - Francis KurkdjianHere, Orange Blossom unveils an unexpected facet, inspired by the fleeting period when the newly-bloomed blossoms exude slightly almondy notes. As its traditional honey-like aromas are subdued, Orange Blossom inhabits the fragrance like a poetic whisper. Its subtly textured floral freshness, upheld by intricate transparency, is an echo of sun-kissed femininity.A fusional Accord of crisp Green Almond unites the blossoms with the bed of vanilla at the perfume s base. An irresistibly light Vanilla Infusion reveals the transparency of the floral notes, which it enshrouds in an addictive aura, creating a soft and luminous sillage.Dressed in an elegant water-green box, the delicately facetted bottle reveals a crystalline green juice. Radiance and transparency resonate like an echo of the original freshness of this new fragrance. L'Eau Couture lets us discover freshness like a promise of new emotions. It invites us to dive into new sensations born of the lightness associated with the newness of spring.The newest fragrance by Elie Saab named Le Parfum L'Eau Couture will be available in 30, 50 and 90ml EDT bottles before Spring 2014.
